I'm tired of these " Jeffree and Nikki quotes"...Respect what's ACTUALLY going on and what is being shared between these two instead of trying to aim for top comment all the time with potentially insensitive comments, because it's like cracking jokes. I think it's terribly sad what Jeffree is going through because if anyone followed him from the beginning (like me, MySpace days), you can definitely tell he had a special connection and love for Nate.
Nikki coming out as transgender, we should also respect that so it's just of sick how people are cracking jokes. It's disrespectful because its a deep and sensitive topic of someone's identity and past. Or of someone present events that hold a huge part of their life.
It's not about (me) being sensitive about the comments, it's just I think the people commenting these "Jeffrey star: Nikki:" comments need to realize how to be more respectful. These two, Jeffree and Nikki are extremely vulnerable right now, sharing massive parts of their lives - although very different from each other - respect should still play a huge factor and showing it I'm sure would be greatly appreciated because these Jeffree/Nikki quote comments are not a form of support.
